name: scljet-write-btree-overflow
description: SclJet M3 multi-leaf B-tree WITH cell overflow — large payloads spill across a table-interior root (cross-backend)
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet multi-leaf B-tree with cell overflow

[ByteSlice, byteSliceToList, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildOverflowBtreeDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)

```scalascript
// Build "a" * n with log-depth recursion (JS has no TCO).
def text(n: Int): String =
  if n <= 0 then ""
  else if n == 1 then "a"
  else
    val half = text(n / 2)
    if n % 2 == 0 then half + half else half + half + "a"

// 28 rows overflow a single 512-byte leaf, so page 2 becomes a table-interior
// root over two leaves (pages 3-4). Row 12 carries a 475-char payload that spills
// onto a one-page overflow chain (page 5) — proving overflow and multi-leaf
// packing compose. 5 pages total; reference integrity_check accepts it and every
// value reads back byte-exact.
def mkRows(i: Int, n: Int, acc: List[List[SqliteValue]]): List[List[SqliteValue]] =
  if i > n then acc.reverse
  else
    val v = if i == 12 then text(475) else "row-value-" + i.toString
    mkRows(i + 1, n, List(SqlInteger(i.toLong), SqlText(v)) :: acc)

buildOverflowBtreeDatabase(512, 1, 1, "t", "CREATE TABLE t(n INTEGER, v TEXT)", mkRows(1, 28, Nil)) match
  case Right(bytes) => println((bytes.length / 512).toString + ":" + byteSliceToList(bytes).toString)
  case Left(error) => println("ERROR:" + error.message)
```
